# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# All variables below are OPTIONAL.
# The skills work in draft-only mode with nothing set: they produce
# the spoken hook script, the caption, and the TikTok settings for you
# to upload in the TikTok app yourself.
# Add a PUBLORA_API_KEY (and a rendered video) to schedule videos.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

# Publora API key - sign up free at https://app.publora.com/signup
PUBLORA_API_KEY=sk_your_key_here

# TikTok platform connection ID (format: tiktok-7123456789)
# Find this in the Publora dashboard: Channels then your TikTok account.
# Copy the whole thing including the tiktok- prefix.
TIKTOK_PLATFORM_ID=tiktok-your_id_here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Apify token (optional) - if you later wire a TikTok-reading actor,
# the read-side skills can fetch a video's stats or transcript instead
# of asking you to paste it. Without a token, the skills fall back to
# asking you to describe the video or paste the script.
#
# Sign up: https://console.apify.com/sign-up
# Token:   https://console.apify.com/settings/integrations
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
APIFY_TOKEN=apify_api_your_token_here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Advanced (Tier 2): if you've built your own poster with Claude Code or
# Codex (e.g. on the official TikTok Content Posting API), set this to the
# command the skills invoke on approval. Leave unset unless you actually
# have a custom poster working.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# TIKTOK_SKILLS_CUSTOM_POSTER=python /path/to/my-poster.py
